# THE ATOM · THE ATOM · techne · the electron cloud · UD0 / techne

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of THE ATOM](the-atom-view.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (THE ATOM's organic-form embodiment): the-atom-view.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** THE ATOM — a techne sphere — the art

**what —** The popular picture of the atom — electrons circling a nucleus like planets — is wrong. Quantum mechanics says an electron has no definite path; it exists as a cloud of probability, an 'orbital,' a shape of where it is likely to be found. The atom is mostly empty space wrapped in fuzz. This sphere draws the honest version: stippled clouds, not rings.

**where —** the art — a generative rendering of a scale  Framework inputs: the scale; the ink; the geometry; the honesty  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** The popular picture of the atom — electrons circling a nucleus like planets — is wrong. Quantum mechanics says an electron has no definite path; it exists as a cloud of probability, an 'orbital,' a shape of where it is likely to be found. The atom is mostly empty space wrapped in fuzz. This sphere draws the honest version: stippled clouds, not rings.

**how —** Original generative art informed by the public record.

**◌ the mythos —** The popular picture of the atom — electrons circling a nucleus like planets — is wrong. Quantum mechanics says an electron has no definite path; it exists as a cloud of probability, an 'orbital,' a shape of where it is likely to be found. The atom is mostly empty space wrapped in fuzz. This sphere draws the honest version: stippled clouds, not rings. a view that cannot be photographed, only drawn

